reviews_data.review_text: Super cute place and lots of seating! However, I got a decaf latte and it was just disappointing. Wasn’t very strong and had a bland taste. Kinda expensive too!

By far the best coffee shop in the Mooresville area! The staff are consistently warm and welcoming, always greeting with a smile. The cozy atmosphere is unmatched, offering a perfect blend of comfort and community. While the products are a little on the pricier side, they're well worth it. I love their seasonal options and pastries!

I really want to emphasize the environment, as I've spent the last few years coming here. Defined coffee has fueled me through my first degree, wedding planning (specifically many hours spent on my vows), home buying stress, and now my second degree. While there are plenty of other coffee shops in the area, none of them compare to the inviting atmosphere and sense of belonging I find at Defined. It’s more than just coffee—it’s a place where life happens.
One of my favorite coffee shops of all time. The flavors they offer are so unique compared to other coffee shops, natural, and delicious.
Cute little coffee shop, love their lattes.
The best place in our little town!
The BEST place for coffee in Charlotte. Great atmosphere, great people, great coffee!
This is by far one of my favorite coffee shops! The coffee is always made well, and served to the brim in big mugs. The staff here are always really nice too.

This is the best coffee spot in Mooresville and surrounding area, by far!
Amazing specialty coffee that is crafted by baristas who genuinely love what they do.
The cozy atmosphere creates a great place to relax, enjoy your drink and eat something from the cafe. Highly recommended!
They have the best and most creative seasonal drinks!

This is probably the best coffee shop ive ever been to, they absolutely know what they're doing in all aspects from sourcing quality and rare beans, roasting, and drink prep. Amazing options. They also make really good baked goods. If you want a good matcha this is the place to go.
Yummy chai tea, great environment
A little pricey but so yummy! The lucky charms macaroon was unique and tasty. I had the salted caramel latte and my partner had the orange matcha. We both thoroughly enjoyed our drinks!
Pastry are so fresh. Blueberry muffin was excellent and moist. Music and volume just right.
This place is another thing!!
Tried the Kilimanjaro coffee, it was fantastic
Good coffee, nice place to plug in and work
Best place for a drip coffee! Great vibes
A lot like a Hallmark Movie place!!  Great place, a bit on the higher price, but it's new...great Coffee and cranberry muffin...

Popular place, hard to find a seat when I was there. Comfortable seating, nice people, high prices. I still don't understand tipping when they don't bring it out. My only complaint. I tipped 15% and they still called my name and left the cup out on the counter like a fast food chain.
Great place for milk drinks, espresso is good with the occasional sour shot. Breakfast items are a safe bet at this place.
great seating options, love the espresso drinks. food menu is solid but can be slow. keep an eye out for your order, because it isn't always clear whose is whose at the pickup counter.
The best chai I’ve had in such a long time. Service is phenomenal. Cute vibe inside. 100% recommend.
Great coffee! Good atmosphere. A bit expensive but worth the price for the quality.
SO WONDERFUL, BEST SERVICE, BEST EXPERIENCE, AMAZING COFFEE, LOVE NAOMI SHE HELPED ME PICK A DELICIOUS CUP OF COFFEE!

This place has some of the best coffee I've ever had! They have a knowledgeable and friendly staff, great food choices, and a good tea selection if coffee isn't your thing. They roast on site, so that's pretty cool to watch as well.
The atmosphere is welcoming and comfortable. Great for both meeting friends or getting some work done.  It's only a couple of miles off of 77 if your driving past Lake Norman, definitely worth the little detour! Highly recommend!
Great coffee shop to visit when I'm in Mooresville.  Great beans.. nice place to sit and relax.
Excellent coffee. Great environment. They even sell their beans for us to enjoy at home!

We serve Defined Coffee at Flywheel Coworking in Concord, and all of our members and guests love it! It makes all the difference when my customers come up to me and say, "That coffee is amazing!" Thanks for making us look great, Defined! TJ is also the best and answers all of my questions, makes recommendations, and clearly loves what he does.
One of the best coffee spots I know. I just wish they would deliver, they would definitely benefit from it.
Wow, great coffee and pastry. Nish  is a great baker, the pumpkin muffin and the ricotta toast are amazing!
Nice place to meet friends.

Unfortunately 3 back to back unpleasant experiences.  Tried it 3 times all 3 had issues. From not serving breakfast till 8, to being out of product to closing early.  Per their advertised hours they should be open till 5:00PM. We arrived at ~4:40 only to learn that the expresso machine had already "been cleaned" and they could not serve us hot coffee as they were shutting down.  We were less than pleased as were the 6 other potential customers that had walked in after us.  As one left we heard them remark "a coffee place that doesn't serve coffee."
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey John, we are sorry you have been unhappy with your experience. If I may, and since this is my first time hearing form you, I will address some of your assertions for clarity. 
1. We do, in fact, serve breakfast. However our kitchen is not open all day since we are primarily a coffee shop. If you wanted to try any of our made to order food items, you can find our kitchen open between 8-2. These kitchen hours are clearly posted on our food menu in the store.  Otherwise we typically have house made muffins available while supplies last.
2. We do sometimes run out of product. We make most of our syrups,  sauces, and many of our pastries- by hand, and we are a small business, therefore we sometimes run out of things. We apologize for the inconvenience and if there was something not to your liking we always appreciate the opportunity to make it right with direct communication. 
3. Our hours are 7:00am-5:00pm Monday through Saturday. These hours do not change except for holidays. If you do not like our regular hours we are sorry to hear that,  but we make drinks from the moment we open to the moment we close without fail.
  In this specific instance you mentioned above,  there appears to have been a misunderstanding  as I can clearly see that a number of customers were served right up to, and even after close with espresso beverages through our pos system. Our barista did explain to one customer that the machine would need a couple minutes to finish a rinse cycle, but she never stated that the espresso machine, or the shop, was permanently closed for the day. We apologize for the misunderstanding. My offer still stands from our email correspondence.
 I hope you have a great rest of your week.

reviews_data.review_text: Recently decided to give this place our business. We've had nothing but customer service issues each time we've gone in.

First class, through and through. I have been a customer for years, back when it started out in Huntersville. Defined is my favorite "third space," hands down. They procure the highest quality beans, roast them in-house, and prioritize fair compensation for the producers! Not only can I get great coffee, it is a great place for community. Work sessions, reading books, hangouts with friends, lattes + card games with my husband -- Defined houses so many of those moments for me. The entire team is beyond wonderful, and Nish (the manager) goes above and beyond to make sure the customer gets a great experience from beginning to end. Expect great coffee, great service, and a great time, every time.

I have been studying at Defined Coffee for the past several weeks. I have gone in 1-2 times per week. I love the atmosphere, that they have plenty of seating and a food menu in addition to coffee and tea and don’t mind people studying and reading.
After having 3 recent similar experiences, I finally decided I needed to leave a review.
There have been 3 separate times that my food order has been incorrect so I’ve needed to approach the counter to try and get what I ordered instead of what I was given. All three times, the gal who appears to be the manager and works in the back preparing the food, has been the person I’ve dealt with. Each time when I’ve kindly explained what I ordered, I was met with a somewhat combative and unfriendly “rebuttal”.  All three times it was the person who is taking the orders who made the error and yet each time I was given an attitude by this manager. Comments along the line of “I don’t have any orders for a BLT” while looking at me, the customer. What am I supposed to do with that? One would think she might turn to the person who takes the orders and inquire where the order is, or even better yet just say “I’ll go make one quickly for you, sorry about that!”… but instead she made it the customers fault by saying she didn’t have the order. I was speechless. So I, the customer, had to turn to the cashier and say “remember, I ordered a BLT…I haven’t gotten it yet”, as if they cannot communicate with each other. It felt as though she intentionally needed to burden me with helping her work through this.
The third time, I ordered a “ English Muffin breakfast sandwich”, was asked no questions and no further information was shared with me when I ordered and this is how it is listed on their menu.  When my order came up, it was eggs only on French bread and about half the size of the English muffin. I approached the counter and kindly said “I ordered the English muffin breakfast sandwich…” the same gal replied to me and said “we don’t have English muffins anymore, it’s in French bread” so I replied “no one explained that to me…and what about the meat?” She replied “you have to ask for it”, I explained that I had never asked for the meat before. She continued by telling me that if no one asks me, that it’s my responsibility to tell them I want meat. I’m assuming this is a new change as the English muffin breakfast sandwich used to come with meat and that’s why I ordered it. So if they have made recent changes to their menu (although it still plainly says “English Muffin”) then one would assume it is their responsibility to inform people of changes they’ve made, especially people who come their frequently and are expecting something different.
There were no apologies, no kindness for the lack of communication, no manners even for that matter. Actually, not even professionalism. It felt like a policy of “the customer is never right” and that I was being treated in a way that would never fly in most businesses I know. I felt like I was being reprimanded.
So I’m not sure who’s running the show here but management needs to get involved and maybe witness first hand how they are treating their customers.
I also want to add that they are charging I think $5.19 for a bag of Earl Grey tea and 11-12 for a breakfast sandwich on French bread that is about 2” x 1.5”.
I will not be returning to this establishment as they have proved to me that they do not care about my business, that clearly they think they can treat people however they want to treat them, have zero concern about the quality of their food or their service and are riding a wave of continued business despite all of this.
Clean and quiet, Defined Coffee is the perfect place to grab a coffee and get some work done. I also got a tasty almond croissant which was larger than anticipated.

Been here a few times to read or do a little work. I like the couple of drinks I’ve tried and some were recommended by the workers based on what I’ve told them I like. The only downside is, like any coffee shop really, it seems there are very specific days and times that it’s not terribly busy. Otherwise it is kind of difficult finding a seat/table. They do otherwise have a variety of seating (some tables/chairs, high top counter, couch). Parking is otherwise readily available as well.
Cute and quiet environment for productive work!

Stopped by for a quick drink and a snack.

It was beautiful inside, the drink was delicious, and reasonably priced.

I’ve grown so fond of Defined of Mooresville. The staff are welcoming and I’m still trying to discover what magic they use when fixing my latte. It’s flavorful, smooth & creamy…just milk & espresso. Quality! They also offer a variety of tasty breakfast items. I do wish they had more lounge-worthy seating though the current options aren’t uncomfortable. You can place an online order through Odeko (they have always had my order right and ready when I get there at the proposed time). 5/5 must try!
Great ambiance and I liked their coffee. I got one of their seasonal drinks, something maple, and it was very good! Not too sweet but not bland. Service was also impeccable!

I’ve been to this coffee shop a few times and always enjoyed their coffee. I usually order to-go, but I’ve been tempted to stay longer because the seating and atmosphere are so inviting.

Today, I grabbed a large vanilla latte, which was delicious as always. However, I also ordered a chocolate croissant, and unfortunately, it was so stale I had to toss it after one bite.

While I’ll definitely return for the great coffee, I’d recommend skipping the baked goods.
Pricey!!!! 😖😫😣 but generally very good. I stop by when I’m in a “treat yoself” type of mood.
I had an iced latte and house-made cranberry muffin. Both were delicious, and the quality was great! Friendly staff and welcoming environment. Easy 5 stars!
The 5 stars for the food is for the COFFEE. This place is beautiful. The staff are so kind and welcoming. I can’t wait to come back here! Espresso and cold brew are delicious!!
Weekly Latte or an Americano 😚🙏
Love their espresso, the staff is always friendly!

I love the coffee here and the people are super friendly, but I don't think I'll be going back.  The last couple of times I've been they have messed up my order.  I asked for a cranberry muffin and they gave me a blueberry muffin that tasted stale.  I usually get my coffee made with oat milk and I've had whole milk added to my coffee instead which is a small mistake but I couldn't drink all my coffee because whole milk upsets my stomach.

Latte, Matcha, blue berry tea.

High quality, fresh, affordable in an excellent environment.
Friendly Staff. Wonderful coffee drinks offered. Their summer special coffee with HINTS of lavender, honey, and orange is amazing.

Wow, I can’t say enough about this coffee shop. It’s amazing! Delicious quality specialty coffee, and unique recipes. Baristas were sweet, skilled, and conversational. Atmosphere was perfection, loved getting to see the roastery, not too
Loud or too quiet in the room, and even a corner space with a couch and kids toys!

Stopped by for the first time today! The vibe is very cute with plenty of seating. I worked for about an hour here and it was a great environment. I had to ask the person at the register to explain the menu to me because I wasn’t really sure how to read it. Unfortunately, she was not the most enthusiastic. I also asked her if she had a recommendation for the food and she said not really. She did say everything was good. I totally get maybe not making a recommendation because you don’t know what people like but the lack of enthusiasm and her tone was not the best. I had the mountaineer coffee with oat milk. Absolutely the star of the show! Beautiful presentation and so good! I ended up with the BLT. It was okay but nothing outstanding. The bread wasn’t really toasted, just warm, and it was around $7 or $8 with no side. I would definitely come back for coffee and probably try something else to eat though. Lastly, when I got up to leave I was going to use their restroom and it was occupied. I noticed a sign that said there were changing tables in the hallway bathroom so I figured I would just go to the hallway. Just be warned that there’s not a sign when you go through that door that shows where to go to find the bathroom. but it’s to the left all the way to the end of the hall. Also, I may have missed it, but I don’t think there was a sign inside of the coffee shop that indicated you would not be able to re-enter the coffee shop through that door. If you were trying to go back into the coffee shop, you would have to go through one of the hallways and around to the front door again to get in. I ended up having to ask another business how to find the bathroom and they told me that the reason that you can’t re-enter that way is due to some issues that they had with vandalism unfortunately. So definitely makes sense as to why they are doing that. Overall I enjoyed the coffee and atmosphere and would return!
The staff is always super friendly and the coffee is amazing consistently I've been to the shop many times and never had nothing short of an amazing experience
Excellent coffee and variety of muffins; service is excellent; and atmosphere is great

Love this coffee shop! Definitely our favorite in the Mooresville area. The baristas + owner are always so friendly + create such a welcoming atmosphere. The coffee + flavors are unique and delicious. And, as a mom, I love the thoughtfulness of having a small area for my kids to play in - huge plus for me!
Great place for coffee, etc.!
The BEST of the best!!!
Went here for a date in January. Matcha not good at all and was cold.
It stinks that your closed on sundays.

This is an amazing place for coffee dates, remote working, or just grabbing a coffee. Every drink I get here is picture perfect AND delicious. They also make some great food and have some fresh pastries. It’s definitely worth a stop in if you’re in if you’re in the area.

The ambiance is soooo peaceful! The moment you walk in is instant comfort. The seating is intentional for all different comfort levels. Absolutely love it! The service is exceptional and the variety of choices on the menu are top tier!
great coffee

The absolute best coffee shop in the Lake Norman area. The coffee/ lattes are spot on, the staff is so friendly, and the ingredients are high quality. The lemon pound cake latte in the summertime is like nothing I’ve ever had. All the lattes are not overly sweet or artificial tasting. I’d visit this coffee shop every single day if it was closer to my house. :)

The absolute best coffee shop in the area. Perfect for studying, a date, or to meet friends. It’s kid friendly, their coffee is incredible, their WiFi is fast, and their staff is kind, attentive, and knowledgeable. I have never had a bad drink or experience or heard of one from my many friends who frequent this location. I’m partial to their chai latte but everything’s good. All you could ask for and I keep coming back

reviews_data.review_text: Fun place, ginger beard latte was excellent!
Always great coffee and service, usually friendly smiling faces, but not always, which is disappointing. 😔
Super cute
amazing specialty coffee! The baristas are always so sweet and helpful! My drink had some pretty latte art too!
High-quality coffee and baristas! I also was recommended a cranberry muffin and they're to die for
Great coffee!!  It is a nice place to socialize.  Great atmosphere!
"My second time at this café, and everything is in order. Excellent service, clean environment, and great coffee preparation. Looking forward to many more visits. Welcome back!"
Great coffee. The customer service is awesome, very friendly and quick to serve. Will return.
Mugs were matte and handles ergonomic. Coffee was great. Might have to share an outlet depending on where you sit. Lots of people coming to work or study.

Always nice to see the folks that know me working there say hi
They make perfect tasting drinking not too sweet but sweet enough.
Great study space, chat space... more serious personal conversation .
Still highly recommended
Great coffee!! Nice music and relaxed setting.
Best place for coffee in Mooresville!

"Today, December 3, 2023, I stumbled upon this charming coffee shop ☕️ purely by chance. Even though it was about to close, I seized the last few minutes to immerse myself in its cozy ambiance. The highlight was the exceptional service from Vanessa, who surprisingly speaks Spanish. I love it when places take that into account, making it much easier for me to place my order, as I don't speak much English. Both girls on duty were fantastic, quick, and very friendly. I will definitely be back soon."
Such a cute place.
By far the BEST latte in all of Mooresville! No matter the flavor it's always balanced and never too sweet. Plus they have the most delicious blueberry muffins.
Reminds me of home. The coffee is amazing, and service is great also!

I love having coffee meetings at Defined Coffee.  Coffee and breakfast items are delish!  The space is large and offers counter or table seating.  There is a little area for children to play or read books.  They roast the beans in-house and you can watch the process through the large glass windows.  It's perfect for meeting a client or enjoying a little work on your own!

I recently had the pleasure of dining at a charming coffee shop that left me utterly enchanted. As I sipped on their maple-infused coffee, I was transported to a cozy, rustic oasis where the aroma of freshly brewed coffee enveloped me in a warm embrace. The maple coffee was a symphony of flavors, where the rich, earthy notes of maple syrup danced in perfect harmony with the robust coffee, creating a delightful contrast of sweetness and warmth.

To accompany this heavenly brew, I indulged in a chocolate muffin that was nothing short of a masterpiece. This delectable delight was like a warm hug for the taste buds. The first bite revealed a moist, chocolatey interior that was both comforting and decadent. Each nibble of the muffin was a journey into a world of velvety cocoa goodness.

What truly set this coffee shop apart was its unique juxtaposition of nature and industry. The interior was adorned with lush green plants, creating an oasis of serenity amidst the hustle and bustle of the city. The combination of exposed brick walls and the vibrant greenery gave the space a distinct character, where the coziness of nature seamlessly met the rugged charm of urban life.

In all, my experience at this coffee shop was a delightful fusion of flavors and atmospheres, making it a place I can't wait to return to for more of their maple coffee and chocolate muffins that warm the soul in the most inviting setting.
Amazing coffee! It was my first time ordering and the girls up front were so helpful. Will be coming back!

This is now my little hidden gem. No only is the atmosphere so quaint but the ladies who work there are so sweet and polite. I came in before the kitchen opened and I need to eat something because of medication I took earlier. I got so caught up on working that I was after 8amand still sitting there without having ordered yet. The lady was so sweet to me and thoughtful. She brought me a small pastry as soon as they were done. I felt so appreciated and cared for. They have a customer for life.
Now, I go at least once a week and I ask either one of my girlfriend to meet me there. If you are ever in the neighborhood and in the mood for some awesome coffee, you have to stop at Defined Coffee😊

Very welcoming and friendly service
Will definitely return soon
Had a lot of booths and so much to look at! Enjoyed it and would have to return back. Very clean and the restrooms were clean as well.

Coffee was very subpar, and over expensive. A nearly $9 bland and not flavorful drink that could’ve been made with a K-Cup. I frequent places like Main Street Coffee Company and Summit, as their prices are fair, and their drinks are amazing. Disappointing every time I go here, as the menu and quality do not improve.

$8.22 for an iced latte and when I asked for the seasonal cold foam on my coffee I was told that it was exclusive to one drink that had to be dine in only. This place never ceases to amaze me. The drink was average. Outrageous prices and ridiculous rules. Every other local coffee shop lets you customize as you please without specifying where you’re going to consume your coffee.
Amazing atmosphere, lovely baristas, and excellent food and drinks. Highly recommend
super nice staff ;) coffee is top notch. Personal recommendation is the Maple Sunrise latte or a traditional cappuccino!
Love this place! Great atmosphere and my new coffee  spot!

Loved this spot! Brought my kids (16, 11, 6 and 6 months) to sit and enjoy some quality time over a cup of lattes and pastries. My husband and I loved our lattes, mine a lemon pound cake latte and his a white chocolate mocha. We loved the service as the ladies were as sweet a the lattes we enjoyed. The cup of art tasted as great as the atmosphere looked. Beautiful spot to enjoy a relaxing afternoon. There was even have a corner for kids! My children stayed busy and quiet as they played checkers and puzzles. We are from out of town and this place was a great find!
It wouldn’t be far fetched to say the best coffee in Mooresville…To each their own but I’d 100% recommend stopping by to give it a shot.
I had a coffee Americano, and cranberry muffin and a chocolate chip muffin. They was delicious. Coffee was very good cost was $14
Best coffee, vibe, and physical set-up in the greater Charlotte area 💯

Handcrafted espresso drinks, comfortable environment, definitely recommend, I'll be back

Update 1: tried an Americano today and really enjoyed how smooth it was.
Not sure I've ever felt so welcomed and wanted at any establishment.
Amazing staff, amazing coffee!
Delicious expresso drinks! Tried both the iced caramel and vanilla lattes, and both were smooth and tasty. Friendly customer service and inviting café space!
Beautiful coffee shop with kind employees. The coffee was good - I would give a 4.5 star.

I went here about a year ago on vacation, but not a day has passed where I haven’t thought about the cranberry muffin I ate here. It was the best muffin I’ve eaten in my life. I also got a really delicious latte with a seasonal flavor that was unlike anything I’ve had before. Really nice service and atmosphere, give this place a try!
Coffee was very good.
If you don't find Defined coffee exquisitely delicious, you don't know good coffee. If youv'e tried the rest.....run and try the best.  Great friendly staff!

It is a very spacious dining area with welcoming decor. Staff were superb! The best cappuccino I had since Italy! Seriously, drinks are well made with quality beans. The pastries are top-notch in my books.
A great place to obtain a tasty cup of hot or cold coffee. The atmosphere is quite chill and relaxing.

I had a delicious fireside chai from their holiday menu (creamy, spicy, and not too sweet). My husband had a maple sunrise latte (which might have been wasted on him since he had a cold, but I thought it was delicious). We got muffins for the whole family. They were all enormous and delicious. We split them into 4ths so we could try different flavors. Peach was my favorite, but it was a tough decision.

The staff was very knowledgeable, friendly, and helpful. It was my first time there and they made sure I got exactly what I wanted.

The location is very accessible. Main door right outside handicapped parking and a ramp cut out to the sidewalk. Lots of open space inside. I'm definitely bringing my sister (who has a power wheelchair) here next time.

Think I found my new favorite coffee shop!
1st visit, had the iced gingerbread latte.  Really good, will be back.

The downtown Mooresville area is home to several coffee shops, but Defined Coffee is a gorgeous place to chat with friends or get some work done. The staff is always friendly, and the drinks are delicious. Depending on the day and time, parking could be better, but overall, I highly recommend stopping by and checking out everything else in that area.

Well, the muffins are delicious, but the drinks are super expensive, and the chai was literally weak tea water with frothed milk on top.
Me personally, a full bodied, well mixed and more nuanced chai is what I consider to be good, but to each their own I suppose.
The interior is well decorated, soft modern music, and overall is a pleasant cafe, if you live off a trust and enjoy talking about veganism, Black Lives Matter, and how much you hate capitalism, while wearing a Northface jacket.
3 stars because the staff does genuinely want to be good at what they do, but they scowl if you ask for whole milk.
Great coffee, excellent ambience, great conversation and unreal internet speeds!
Great Coffee!!! and even better people!
This is the best coffee I have ever had it’s amazing I have signed up for the subscription so I can always have fresh coffee that is well roasted
What a wonderful coffee and what a great place and wonderful people excellent service one of the best coffee I had in my life
Cozy atmosphere and great flavors!
Nice atmosphere with wonderful staff.
Very calm atmosphere. Their coffee and hot chocolate is very good!

I ordered a latte with almond milk and cinnamon. I was very happy that they had cinnamon in powder and not a syrup. They steamed the almond milk with the cinnamon and it was probably the best latte I have ever had. Service was awesome and coffee is perfect.

My daughter and I wanted to grab a small snack and a coffee. Beautiful atmosphere and friendly staff. I was looking forward to trying this new coffee place. Unfortunately it is was too pricey to stay.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Tanya! We're sorry you didn't get to try anything from our menu. We pride ourselves in serving a premium product that we believe is worth every penny. If you'd like to stop back in again to sample some of what we have to offer on the house just let us know. Have a great day!
staff@definedcoffee.com

reviews_data.review_text: I have checked out this cafe twice and while it’s a bit pricey I think it’s all worth it. It’s a bit loud at times but I’m still able to focus and get work done which is the main goal. Thanks for the great customer service!!

I grew up in Mooresville but left 18 years ago and currently live in Portland, OR. It’s encouraging to finally see coffee of this caliber coming to my hometown. I’ll definitely be a regular when visiting family.
A must visit. Sweet vibes. Good food. Amazing espresso drinks.

Great little coffee shop in Mooresville with very friendly staff. They roast their own beans here making for extremely tasty drinks. Lots of comfy seating here as well so it’s a great place to hunker down and do some work or meet up with a friend.

Definitely try one of their specialty lattes, or, if you want a twist on one you see, they’re happy so accommodate. They made me a hot orange mocha (don’t knock it till you try it) and it was incredible. I would definitely recommend if you’re passing through Mooresville.
Friendly staff. I can't rate the coffee, I don't drink it. But I love the Blueberry muffins.
Nice layout, chill music, quiet competence making my latte. Roasting on Tuesdays around noon.
I love this place. Such high quality coffee, the flavors are amazing, staff is always so friendly, and the baked goods are delicious! My new favorite coffee place!
Very kind staff, beautiful atmosphere, and the drinks are incredible. Such a beautiful approach to handcrafted drinks.

Absolutely beautiful space. Tranquil comfortable elegant. Barista team is welcoming and knows their coffee. Looking forward to making this a regular rotation. Quite possibly one of the best drinks I’ve had in North Carolina so far. Balanced full flavor.
Nice place, excellent coffee, but, my double espresso was no good. It takes 18 seconds to brew a double shot. They should try it this way.

Decent coffee. Friendly service.cute interior design.
Drinks are  Overpriced.
Online ordering doesn’t work.

Iced 20 oz latte almost $8.00
Iced Americano 20oz (3-espresso) Almost $7.00
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi MJH, thanks for taking the time to leave us a review! We're sorry you had trouble with our mobile ordering on Odeko. Can you please send us an email to let us know what went wrong? Support for Odeko is very responsive so we hopeful we can get it resolved. Also, you can view our prices through Odeko as well. Our 20oz iced latte and triple shot Americano both start at $5.50 plus tax. We're always happy to ensure you were charged accurately so please let us know the details in your email. We really hope you'll come back again! Thanks!
-Keifer, Olivia, and the Mooresville crew.
mooresville@definedcoffee.com

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to grab some joe!
Beautiful atmosphere, friendly staff, masterful espresso drinks. Defined Coffee is based.
Hands down the best coffee I’ve had in Mooresville! Atmosphere is calm and relaxed and everyone was very polite and helpful! Will definitely be coming back!

I came in and got the gingerbread latte. It was absolutely brilliant. The two people working were super helpful / friendly on helping what I should choose. Would highly recommend them for your morning coffee!

This place has such a relaxing vibe to it. Service was amazing and the coffee was even better. I got the vanilla lavender latte and it was the best latte I think I’ve ever had. Definitely would recommend for a comfy afternoon coffee or a work spot!

As a Washington transplant I am always looking for a great cup of coffee that has that Seattle vibe. Try this place- you won’t be disappointed. The atmosphere is inviting and comfortable for a work visit or catching up with friends. The coffee was the best I have had in quite a while. As a bonus- everyone who was working was friendly, asked questions to make sure we were getting just the right mix and we can’t wait to go back.

This was my first time visiting. Everybody was super friendly and easy to talk to.

There was plenty of comfy seating available while I enjoyed my yummy Maple Sunrise Latte.

I LOVE that they use real ceramic coffee mugs when you dine in.  Definitely a special touch that a lot of coffee shops have lost using all paper products.

I'll definitely be back!
Amazing coffee and lovely staff
Good coffee, neat place just, a little too big and loud for me.

In town visiting fam and stopped in for a quick coffee. Love the space and the employees are great.

The coffee wasn't my favorite.  Definitely on the more expensive end.

I usually take light cream in my coffee but don't recommend doing that here. The Americano was so hot that it did something funky with the cream and didn't taste great. I went back in, and they happily made me a new drink and didn't add cream.
Atmosphere was so warm and relaxing. Beautiful inside. Coffee was great and the staff was wonderful. This will be our new local coffee shop we go to.

One of the nicest coffee shops I've ever been to as far as the interior and atmosphere are concerned. The coffee was on par with any good local coffee shop I've been to.

The coffee is good, and the service and location are great.
The best coffee in the greater Charlotte area, hands down.
One of the best lattes I’ve ever had in the US. Definitely a must. Their Mountaineer is delicious.

Perfect Coffee and Perfect Venue. Coffee doesnt come any better than this. The shop has every attention to detail including the super comfy chairs at the window. Its a destination that suits those that work in coffee shops instead of at home as well as a casual meeting place for friends and co workers. Did I mention the coffee is to die for.

What a cute place. The space is open and relaxing with still plenty of places to sit and have  some privacy. Coffee was phenomenal. I got an almond milk cappuccino and it was sooo good. Stop by if you can!
I had coffee with a friend. My first time at Defined Coffee. Delicious products and quaint atmosphere. I'll be back soon.

Love this place and their love of coffee shines! Beautifully decorated, family friendly and willing to help someone with decidaphobia pick from their seasonal coffees…and I’ve love every one. Their pumpkin flavor is my favorite right now.

Very friendly service, great open space.  Lots of places to work on an electronic device and plugs close by the seating.  Chill vibe with open windows for natural lighting.  Tried a lovely hot tea while there.
Love this place! It’s beautiful, relaxing and welcoming! The drinks are delicious as well!

Defined coffee’s 3rd location is an outstanding one! They have started to roast their beans! The coffee is perfection. The atmosphere is ideal for a quick stop or a work from coffee-shop experience. The baristas are awesome, dedicated employees that are loyal to the brand and company. I can’t wait to bring people in here. Such a great job everyone!
Best coffee shop in Mooresville, hands down!!

Best cup of coffee I've had since moving to the Charlotte area. Kindest, most knowledgeable, and accommodating staff I've encountered at any establishment in the area.  And top notch design & aesthetic!
The best coffee in the Lake Norman area. Seeing the roaster inside the shop is also really cool! You get to see how the whole process happens
Great coffee and atmosphere! The staff was very welcoming. Great spot to get some work done or just chill out!
The best coffee around! Lovely atmosphere! Great place for a playdate. They have a little kids section with books and puzzles and comfy bean bag seats!

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute place and lots of seating! However, I got a decaf latte and it was just disappointing. Wasn’t very strong and had a bland taste. Kinda expensive too!

By far the best coffee shop in the Mooresville area! The staff are consistently warm and welcoming, always greeting with a smile. The cozy atmosphere is unmatched, offering a perfect blend of comfort and community. While the products are a little on the pricier side, they're well worth it. I love their seasonal options and pastries!

I really want to emphasize the environment, as I've spent the last few years coming here. Defined coffee has fueled me through my first degree, wedding planning (specifically many hours spent on my vows), home buying stress, and now my second degree. While there are plenty of other coffee shops in the area, none of them compare to the inviting atmosphere and sense of belonging I find at Defined. It’s more than just coffee—it’s a place where life happens.
One of my favorite coffee shops of all time. The flavors they offer are so unique compared to other coffee shops, natural, and delicious.
Cute little coffee shop, love their lattes.
The best place in our little town!
The BEST place for coffee in Charlotte. Great atmosphere, great people, great coffee!
This is by far one of my favorite coffee shops! The coffee is always made well, and served to the brim in big mugs. The staff here are always really nice too.

This is the best coffee spot in Mooresville and surrounding area, by far!
Amazing specialty coffee that is crafted by baristas who genuinely love what they do.
The cozy atmosphere creates a great place to relax, enjoy your drink and eat something from the cafe. Highly recommended!
They have the best and most creative seasonal drinks!

This is probably the best coffee shop ive ever been to, they absolutely know what they're doing in all aspects from sourcing quality and rare beans, roasting, and drink prep. Amazing options. They also make really good baked goods. If you want a good matcha this is the place to go.
Yummy chai tea, great environment
A little pricey but so yummy! The lucky charms macaroon was unique and tasty. I had the salted caramel latte and my partner had the orange matcha. We both thoroughly enjoyed our drinks!
Pastry are so fresh. Blueberry muffin was excellent and moist. Music and volume just right.
This place is another thing!!
Tried the Kilimanjaro coffee, it was fantastic
Good coffee, nice place to plug in and work
Best place for a drip coffee! Great vibes
A lot like a Hallmark Movie place!!  Great place, a bit on the higher price, but it's new...great Coffee and cranberry muffin...

Popular place, hard to find a seat when I was there. Comfortable seating, nice people, high prices. I still don't understand tipping when they don't bring it out. My only complaint. I tipped 15% and they still called my name and left the cup out on the counter like a fast food chain.
Great place for milk drinks, espresso is good with the occasional sour shot. Breakfast items are a safe bet at this place.
great seating options, love the espresso drinks. food menu is solid but can be slow. keep an eye out for your order, because it isn't always clear whose is whose at the pickup counter.
The best chai I’ve had in such a long time. Service is phenomenal. Cute vibe inside. 100% recommend.
Great coffee! Good atmosphere. A bit expensive but worth the price for the quality.
SO WONDERFUL, BEST SERVICE, BEST EXPERIENCE, AMAZING COFFEE, LOVE NAOMI SHE HELPED ME PICK A DELICIOUS CUP OF COFFEE!

This place has some of the best coffee I've ever had! They have a knowledgeable and friendly staff, great food choices, and a good tea selection if coffee isn't your thing. They roast on site, so that's pretty cool to watch as well.
The atmosphere is welcoming and comfortable. Great for both meeting friends or getting some work done.  It's only a couple of miles off of 77 if your driving past Lake Norman, definitely worth the little detour! Highly recommend!
Great coffee shop to visit when I'm in Mooresville.  Great beans.. nice place to sit and relax.
Excellent coffee. Great environment. They even sell their beans for us to enjoy at home!

We serve Defined Coffee at Flywheel Coworking in Concord, and all of our members and guests love it! It makes all the difference when my customers come up to me and say, "That coffee is amazing!" Thanks for making us look great, Defined! TJ is also the best and answers all of my questions, makes recommendations, and clearly loves what he does.
One of the best coffee spots I know. I just wish they would deliver, they would definitely benefit from it.
Wow, great coffee and pastry. Nish  is a great baker, the pumpkin muffin and the ricotta toast are amazing!
Nice place to meet friends.

Unfortunately 3 back to back unpleasant experiences.  Tried it 3 times all 3 had issues. From not serving breakfast till 8, to being out of product to closing early.  Per their advertised hours they should be open till 5:00PM. We arrived at ~4:40 only to learn that the expresso machine had already "been cleaned" and they could not serve us hot coffee as they were shutting down.  We were less than pleased as were the 6 other potential customers that had walked in after us.  As one left we heard them remark "a coffee place that doesn't serve coffee."
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey John, we are sorry you have been unhappy with your experience. If I may, and since this is my first time hearing form you, I will address some of your assertions for clarity. 
1. We do, in fact, serve breakfast. However our kitchen is not open all day since we are primarily a coffee shop. If you wanted to try any of our made to order food items, you can find our kitchen open between 8-2. These kitchen hours are clearly posted on our food menu in the store.  Otherwise we typically have house made muffins available while supplies last.
2. We do sometimes run out of product. We make most of our syrups,  sauces, and many of our pastries- by hand, and we are a small business, therefore we sometimes run out of things. We apologize for the inconvenience and if there was something not to your liking we always appreciate the opportunity to make it right with direct communication. 
3. Our hours are 7:00am-5:00pm Monday through Saturday. These hours do not change except for holidays. If you do not like our regular hours we are sorry to hear that,  but we make drinks from the moment we open to the moment we close without fail.
  In this specific instance you mentioned above,  there appears to have been a misunderstanding  as I can clearly see that a number of customers were served right up to, and even after close with espresso beverages through our pos system. Our barista did explain to one customer that the machine would need a couple minutes to finish a rinse cycle, but she never stated that the espresso machine, or the shop, was permanently closed for the day. We apologize for the misunderstanding. My offer still stands from our email correspondence.
 I hope you have a great rest of your week.

reviews_data.review_text: Recently decided to give this place our business. We've had nothing but customer service issues each time we've gone in.

First class, through and through. I have been a customer for years, back when it started out in Huntersville. Defined is my favorite "third space," hands down. They procure the highest quality beans, roast them in-house, and prioritize fair compensation for the producers! Not only can I get great coffee, it is a great place for community. Work sessions, reading books, hangouts with friends, lattes + card games with my husband -- Defined houses so many of those moments for me. The entire team is beyond wonderful, and Nish (the manager) goes above and beyond to make sure the customer gets a great experience from beginning to end. Expect great coffee, great service, and a great time, every time.

I have been studying at Defined Coffee for the past several weeks. I have gone in 1-2 times per week. I love the atmosphere, that they have plenty of seating and a food menu in addition to coffee and tea and don’t mind people studying and reading.
After having 3 recent similar experiences, I finally decided I needed to leave a review.
There have been 3 separate times that my food order has been incorrect so I’ve needed to approach the counter to try and get what I ordered instead of what I was given. All three times, the gal who appears to be the manager and works in the back preparing the food, has been the person I’ve dealt with. Each time when I’ve kindly explained what I ordered, I was met with a somewhat combative and unfriendly “rebuttal”.  All three times it was the person who is taking the orders who made the error and yet each time I was given an attitude by this manager. Comments along the line of “I don’t have any orders for a BLT” while looking at me, the customer. What am I supposed to do with that? One would think she might turn to the person who takes the orders and inquire where the order is, or even better yet just say “I’ll go make one quickly for you, sorry about that!”… but instead she made it the customers fault by saying she didn’t have the order. I was speechless. So I, the customer, had to turn to the cashier and say “remember, I ordered a BLT…I haven’t gotten it yet”, as if they cannot communicate with each other. It felt as though she intentionally needed to burden me with helping her work through this.
The third time, I ordered a “ English Muffin breakfast sandwich”, was asked no questions and no further information was shared with me when I ordered and this is how it is listed on their menu.  When my order came up, it was eggs only on French bread and about half the size of the English muffin. I approached the counter and kindly said “I ordered the English muffin breakfast sandwich…” the same gal replied to me and said “we don’t have English muffins anymore, it’s in French bread” so I replied “no one explained that to me…and what about the meat?” She replied “you have to ask for it”, I explained that I had never asked for the meat before. She continued by telling me that if no one asks me, that it’s my responsibility to tell them I want meat. I’m assuming this is a new change as the English muffin breakfast sandwich used to come with meat and that’s why I ordered it. So if they have made recent changes to their menu (although it still plainly says “English Muffin”) then one would assume it is their responsibility to inform people of changes they’ve made, especially people who come their frequently and are expecting something different.
There were no apologies, no kindness for the lack of communication, no manners even for that matter. Actually, not even professionalism. It felt like a policy of “the customer is never right” and that I was being treated in a way that would never fly in most businesses I know. I felt like I was being reprimanded.
So I’m not sure who’s running the show here but management needs to get involved and maybe witness first hand how they are treating their customers.
I also want to add that they are charging I think $5.19 for a bag of Earl Grey tea and 11-12 for a breakfast sandwich on French bread that is about 2” x 1.5”.
I will not be returning to this establishment as they have proved to me that they do not care about my business, that clearly they think they can treat people however they want to treat them, have zero concern about the quality of their food or their service and are riding a wave of continued business despite all of this.
Clean and quiet, Defined Coffee is the perfect place to grab a coffee and get some work done. I also got a tasty almond croissant which was larger than anticipated.

Been here a few times to read or do a little work. I like the couple of drinks I’ve tried and some were recommended by the workers based on what I’ve told them I like. The only downside is, like any coffee shop really, it seems there are very specific days and times that it’s not terribly busy. Otherwise it is kind of difficult finding a seat/table. They do otherwise have a variety of seating (some tables/chairs, high top counter, couch). Parking is otherwise readily available as well.
Cute and quiet environment for productive work!

Stopped by for a quick drink and a snack.

It was beautiful inside, the drink was delicious, and reasonably priced.

I’ve grown so fond of Defined of Mooresville. The staff are welcoming and I’m still trying to discover what magic they use when fixing my latte. It’s flavorful, smooth & creamy…just milk & espresso. Quality! They also offer a variety of tasty breakfast items. I do wish they had more lounge-worthy seating though the current options aren’t uncomfortable. You can place an online order through Odeko (they have always had my order right and ready when I get there at the proposed time). 5/5 must try!
Great ambiance and I liked their coffee. I got one of their seasonal drinks, something maple, and it was very good! Not too sweet but not bland. Service was also impeccable!

I’ve been to this coffee shop a few times and always enjoyed their coffee. I usually order to-go, but I’ve been tempted to stay longer because the seating and atmosphere are so inviting.

Today, I grabbed a large vanilla latte, which was delicious as always. However, I also ordered a chocolate croissant, and unfortunately, it was so stale I had to toss it after one bite.

While I’ll definitely return for the great coffee, I’d recommend skipping the baked goods.
Pricey!!!! 😖😫😣 but generally very good. I stop by when I’m in a “treat yoself” type of mood.
I had an iced latte and house-made cranberry muffin. Both were delicious, and the quality was great! Friendly staff and welcoming environment. Easy 5 stars!
The 5 stars for the food is for the COFFEE. This place is beautiful. The staff are so kind and welcoming. I can’t wait to come back here! Espresso and cold brew are delicious!!
Weekly Latte or an Americano 😚🙏
Love their espresso, the staff is always friendly!

I love the coffee here and the people are super friendly, but I don't think I'll be going back.  The last couple of times I've been they have messed up my order.  I asked for a cranberry muffin and they gave me a blueberry muffin that tasted stale.  I usually get my coffee made with oat milk and I've had whole milk added to my coffee instead which is a small mistake but I couldn't drink all my coffee because whole milk upsets my stomach.

Latte, Matcha, blue berry tea.

High quality, fresh, affordable in an excellent environment.
Friendly Staff. Wonderful coffee drinks offered. Their summer special coffee with HINTS of lavender, honey, and orange is amazing.

Wow, I can’t say enough about this coffee shop. It’s amazing! Delicious quality specialty coffee, and unique recipes. Baristas were sweet, skilled, and conversational. Atmosphere was perfection, loved getting to see the roastery, not too
Loud or too quiet in the room, and even a corner space with a couch and kids toys!

Stopped by for the first time today! The vibe is very cute with plenty of seating. I worked for about an hour here and it was a great environment. I had to ask the person at the register to explain the menu to me because I wasn’t really sure how to read it. Unfortunately, she was not the most enthusiastic. I also asked her if she had a recommendation for the food and she said not really. She did say everything was good. I totally get maybe not making a recommendation because you don’t know what people like but the lack of enthusiasm and her tone was not the best. I had the mountaineer coffee with oat milk. Absolutely the star of the show! Beautiful presentation and so good! I ended up with the BLT. It was okay but nothing outstanding. The bread wasn’t really toasted, just warm, and it was around $7 or $8 with no side. I would definitely come back for coffee and probably try something else to eat though. Lastly, when I got up to leave I was going to use their restroom and it was occupied. I noticed a sign that said there were changing tables in the hallway bathroom so I figured I would just go to the hallway. Just be warned that there’s not a sign when you go through that door that shows where to go to find the bathroom. but it’s to the left all the way to the end of the hall. Also, I may have missed it, but I don’t think there was a sign inside of the coffee shop that indicated you would not be able to re-enter the coffee shop through that door. If you were trying to go back into the coffee shop, you would have to go through one of the hallways and around to the front door again to get in. I ended up having to ask another business how to find the bathroom and they told me that the reason that you can’t re-enter that way is due to some issues that they had with vandalism unfortunately. So definitely makes sense as to why they are doing that. Overall I enjoyed the coffee and atmosphere and would return!
The staff is always super friendly and the coffee is amazing consistently I've been to the shop many times and never had nothing short of an amazing experience
Excellent coffee and variety of muffins; service is excellent; and atmosphere is great

Love this coffee shop! Definitely our favorite in the Mooresville area. The baristas + owner are always so friendly + create such a welcoming atmosphere. The coffee + flavors are unique and delicious. And, as a mom, I love the thoughtfulness of having a small area for my kids to play in - huge plus for me!
Great place for coffee, etc.!
The BEST of the best!!!
Went here for a date in January. Matcha not good at all and was cold.
It stinks that your closed on sundays.

This is an amazing place for coffee dates, remote working, or just grabbing a coffee. Every drink I get here is picture perfect AND delicious. They also make some great food and have some fresh pastries. It’s definitely worth a stop in if you’re in if you’re in the area.

The ambiance is soooo peaceful! The moment you walk in is instant comfort. The seating is intentional for all different comfort levels. Absolutely love it! The service is exceptional and the variety of choices on the menu are top tier!
great coffee

The absolute best coffee shop in the Lake Norman area. The coffee/ lattes are spot on, the staff is so friendly, and the ingredients are high quality. The lemon pound cake latte in the summertime is like nothing I’ve ever had. All the lattes are not overly sweet or artificial tasting. I’d visit this coffee shop every single day if it was closer to my house. :)

The absolute best coffee shop in the area. Perfect for studying, a date, or to meet friends. It’s kid friendly, their coffee is incredible, their WiFi is fast, and their staff is kind, attentive, and knowledgeable. I have never had a bad drink or experience or heard of one from my many friends who frequent this location. I’m partial to their chai latte but everything’s good. All you could ask for and I keep coming back

Super cute
amazing specialty coffee! The baristas are always so sweet and helpful! My drink had some pretty latte art too!

"My second time at this café, and everything is in order. Excellent service, clean environment, and great coffee preparation. Looking forward to many more visits. Welcome back!"
Great coffee. The customer service is awesome, very friendly and quick to serve. Will return.
Mugs were matte and handles ergonomic. Coffee was great. Might have to share an outlet depending on where you sit. Lots of people coming to work or study.

Always nice to see the folks that know me working there say hi
They make perfect tasting drinking not too sweet but sweet enough.

Still highly recommended
Great coffee!! Nice music and relaxed setting.
Best place for coffee in Mooresville!

"Today, December 3, 2023, I stumbled upon this charming coffee shop ☕️ purely by chance. Even though it was about to close, I seized the last few minutes to immerse myself in its cozy ambiance. The highlight was the exceptional service from Vanessa, who surprisingly speaks Spanish. I love it when places take that into account, making it much easier for me to place my order, as I don't speak much English. Both girls on duty were fantastic, quick, and very friendly. I will definitely be back soon."
Such a cute place.
By far the BEST latte in all of Mooresville! No matter the flavor it's always balanced and never too sweet. Plus they have the most delicious blueberry muffins.
Reminds me of home. The coffee is amazing, and service is great also!

I love having coffee meetings at Defined Coffee.  Coffee and breakfast items are delish!  The space is large and offers counter or table seating.  There is a little area for children to play or read books.  They roast the beans in-house and you can watch the process through the large glass windows.  It's perfect for meeting a client or enjoying a little work on your own!

I recently had the pleasure of dining at a charming coffee shop that left me utterly enchanted. As I sipped on their maple-infused coffee, I was transported to a cozy, rustic oasis where the aroma of freshly brewed coffee enveloped me in a warm embrace. The maple coffee was a symphony of flavors, where the rich, earthy notes of maple syrup danced in perfect harmony with the robust coffee, creating a delightful contrast of sweetness and warmth.

To accompany this heavenly brew, I indulged in a chocolate muffin that was nothing short of a masterpiece. This delectable delight was like a warm hug for the taste buds. The first bite revealed a moist, chocolatey interior that was both comforting and decadent. Each nibble of the muffin was a journey into a world of velvety cocoa goodness.

What truly set this coffee shop apart was its unique juxtaposition of nature and industry. The interior was adorned with lush green plants, creating an oasis of serenity amidst the hustle and bustle of the city. The combination of exposed brick walls and the vibrant greenery gave the space a distinct character, where the coziness of nature seamlessly met the rugged charm of urban life.

In all, my experience at this coffee shop was a delightful fusion of flavors and atmospheres, making it a place I can't wait to return to for more of their maple coffee and chocolate muffins that warm the soul in the most inviting setting.
Amazing coffee! It was my first time ordering and the girls up front were so helpful. Will be coming back!

This is now my little hidden gem. No only is the atmosphere so quaint but the ladies who work there are so sweet and polite. I came in before the kitchen opened and I need to eat something because of medication I took earlier. I got so caught up on working that I was after 8amand still sitting there without having ordered yet. The lady was so sweet to me and thoughtful. She brought me a small pastry as soon as they were done. I felt so appreciated and cared for. They have a customer for life.
Now, I go at least once a week and I ask either one of my girlfriend to meet me there. If you are ever in the neighborhood and in the mood for some awesome coffee, you have to stop at Defined Coffee😊

Very welcoming and friendly service
Will definitely return soon
Had a lot of booths and so much to look at! Enjoyed it and would have to return back. Very clean and the restrooms were clean as well.

Coffee was very subpar, and over expensive. A nearly $9 bland and not flavorful drink that could’ve been made with a K-Cup. I frequent places like Main Street Coffee Company and Summit, as their prices are fair, and their drinks are amazing. Disappointing every time I go here, as the menu and quality do not improve.

$8.22 for an iced latte and when I asked for the seasonal cold foam on my coffee I was told that it was exclusive to one drink that had to be dine in only. This place never ceases to amaze me. The drink was average. Outrageous prices and ridiculous rules. Every other local coffee shop lets you customize as you please without specifying where you’re going to consume your coffee.
Amazing atmosphere, lovely baristas, and excellent food and drinks. Highly recommend
super nice staff ;) coffee is top notch. Personal recommendation is the Maple Sunrise latte or a traditional cappuccino!
Love this place! Great atmosphere and my new coffee  spot!

Loved this spot! Brought my kids (16, 11, 6 and 6 months) to sit and enjoy some quality time over a cup of lattes and pastries. My husband and I loved our lattes, mine a lemon pound cake latte and his a white chocolate mocha. We loved the service as the ladies were as sweet a the lattes we enjoyed. The cup of art tasted as great as the atmosphere looked. Beautiful spot to enjoy a relaxing afternoon. There was even have a corner for kids! My children stayed busy and quiet as they played checkers and puzzles. We are from out of town and this place was a great find!
It wouldn’t be far fetched to say the best coffee in Mooresville…To each their own but I’d 100% recommend stopping by to give it a shot.
I had a coffee Americano, and cranberry muffin and a chocolate chip muffin. They was delicious. Coffee was very good cost was $14
Best coffee, vibe, and physical set-up in the greater Charlotte area 💯

Handcrafted espresso drinks, comfortable environment, definitely recommend, I'll be back

Update 1: tried an Americano today and really enjoyed how smooth it was.
Not sure I've ever felt so welcomed and wanted at any establishment.
Amazing staff, amazing coffee!
Delicious expresso drinks! Tried both the iced caramel and vanilla lattes, and both were smooth and tasty. Friendly customer service and inviting café space!
Beautiful coffee shop with kind employees. The coffee was good - I would give a 4.5 star.

I went here about a year ago on vacation, but not a day has passed where I haven’t thought about the cranberry muffin I ate here. It was the best muffin I’ve eaten in my life. I also got a really delicious latte with a seasonal flavor that was unlike anything I’ve had before. Really nice service and atmosphere, give this place a try!
Coffee was very good.
If you don't find Defined coffee exquisitely delicious, you don't know good coffee. If youv'e tried the rest.....run and try the best.  Great friendly staff!

It is a very spacious dining area with welcoming decor. Staff were superb! The best cappuccino I had since Italy! Seriously, drinks are well made with quality beans. The pastries are top-notch in my books.
A great place to obtain a tasty cup of hot or cold coffee. The atmosphere is quite chill and relaxing.

I had a delicious fireside chai from their holiday menu (creamy, spicy, and not too sweet). My husband had a maple sunrise latte (which might have been wasted on him since he had a cold, but I thought it was delicious). We got muffins for the whole family. They were all enormous and delicious. We split them into 4ths so we could try different flavors. Peach was my favorite, but it was a tough decision.

The staff was very knowledgeable, friendly, and helpful. It was my first time there and they made sure I got exactly what I wanted.

The location is very accessible. Main door right outside handicapped parking and a ramp cut out to the sidewalk. Lots of open space inside. I'm definitely bringing my sister (who has a power wheelchair) here next time.

Think I found my new favorite coffee shop!
1st visit, had the iced gingerbread latte.  Really good, will be back.

The downtown Mooresville area is home to several coffee shops, but Defined Coffee is a gorgeous place to chat with friends or get some work done. The staff is always friendly, and the drinks are delicious. Depending on the day and time, parking could be better, but overall, I highly recommend stopping by and checking out everything else in that area.

Well, the muffins are delicious, but the drinks are super expensive, and the chai was literally weak tea water with frothed milk on top.
Me personally, a full bodied, well mixed and more nuanced chai is what I consider to be good, but to each their own I suppose.
The interior is well decorated, soft modern music, and overall is a pleasant cafe, if you live off a trust and enjoy talking about veganism, Black Lives Matter, and how much you hate capitalism, while wearing a Northface jacket.
3 stars because the staff does genuinely want to be good at what they do, but they scowl if you ask for whole milk.
Great coffee, excellent ambience, great conversation and unreal internet speeds!
Great Coffee!!! and even better people!
This is the best coffee I have ever had it’s amazing I have signed up for the subscription so I can always have fresh coffee that is well roasted
What a wonderful coffee and what a great place and wonderful people excellent service one of the best coffee I had in my life
Cozy atmosphere and great flavors!
Nice atmosphere with wonderful staff.
Very calm atmosphere. Their coffee and hot chocolate is very good!

I ordered a latte with almond milk and cinnamon. I was very happy that they had cinnamon in powder and not a syrup. They steamed the almond milk with the cinnamon and it was probably the best latte I have ever had. Service was awesome and coffee is perfect.

My daughter and I wanted to grab a small snack and a coffee. Beautiful atmosphere and friendly staff. I was looking forward to trying this new coffee place. Unfortunately it is was too pricey to stay.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Tanya! We're sorry you didn't get to try anything from our menu. We pride ourselves in serving a premium product that we believe is worth every penny. If you'd like to stop back in again to sample some of what we have to offer on the house just let us know. Have a great day!
staff@definedcoffee.com

reviews_data.review_text: I have checked out this cafe twice and while it’s a bit pricey I think it’s all worth it. It’s a bit loud at times but I’m still able to focus and get work done which is the main goal. Thanks for the great customer service!!

I grew up in Mooresville but left 18 years ago and currently live in Portland, OR. It’s encouraging to finally see coffee of this caliber coming to my hometown. I’ll definitely be a regular when visiting family.
A must visit. Sweet vibes. Good food. Amazing espresso drinks.

Great little coffee shop in Mooresville with very friendly staff. They roast their own beans here making for extremely tasty drinks. Lots of comfy seating here as well so it’s a great place to hunker down and do some work or meet up with a friend.

Definitely try one of their specialty lattes, or, if you want a twist on one you see, they’re happy so accommodate. They made me a hot orange mocha (don’t knock it till you try it) and it was incredible. I would definitely recommend if you’re passing through Mooresville.
Friendly staff. I can't rate the coffee, I don't drink it. But I love the Blueberry muffins.
Nice layout, chill music, quiet competence making my latte. Roasting on Tuesdays around noon.
I love this place. Such high quality coffee, the flavors are amazing, staff is always so friendly, and the baked goods are delicious! My new favorite coffee place!
Very kind staff, beautiful atmosphere, and the drinks are incredible. Such a beautiful approach to handcrafted drinks.

Absolutely beautiful space. Tranquil comfortable elegant. Barista team is welcoming and knows their coffee. Looking forward to making this a regular rotation. Quite possibly one of the best drinks I’ve had in North Carolina so far. Balanced full flavor.
Nice place, excellent coffee, but, my double espresso was no good. It takes 18 seconds to brew a double shot. They should try it this way.

Decent coffee. Friendly service.cute interior design.
Drinks are  Overpriced.
Online ordering doesn’t work.

Iced 20 oz latte almost $8.00
Iced Americano 20oz (3-espresso) Almost $7.00
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi MJH, thanks for taking the time to leave us a review! We're sorry you had trouble with our mobile ordering on Odeko. Can you please send us an email to let us know what went wrong? Support for Odeko is very responsive so we hopeful we can get it resolved. Also, you can view our prices through Odeko as well. Our 20oz iced latte and triple shot Americano both start at $5.50 plus tax. We're always happy to ensure you were charged accurately so please let us know the details in your email. We really hope you'll come back again! Thanks!
-Keifer, Olivia, and the Mooresville crew.
mooresville@definedcoffee.com

reviews_data.review_text:
Beautiful and very nice shop. The espresso and drinks were lovely, however a bit expensive.

We spent about $17 on two large drinks here.
Best flavored coffee I have ever tried.
Place slaps
Super nice and friendly staff along with a great and attractive coffee shop environment.

So lovely every time. Workers are very friendly :)
I really love the Matcha tea!

I’m
Sure it’s good but unable to try. It’s definitely not open late though. It closed at 5pm not midnite. Hours need to be updated google

reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Michael, thanks for pointing that out! We were closed for electrical work this morning and there was a typo in our temporary hours. We've gone ahead and fixed it and invite you in for a drink on us! Thanks again and sorry for the inconvenience!

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to grab some joe!
Beautiful atmosphere, friendly staff, masterful espresso drinks. Defined Coffee is based.
Hands down the best coffee I’ve had in Mooresville! Atmosphere is calm and relaxed and everyone was very polite and helpful! Will definitely be coming back!

I came in and got the gingerbread latte. It was absolutely brilliant. The two people working were super helpful / friendly on helping what I should choose. Would highly recommend them for your morning coffee!

This place has such a relaxing vibe to it. Service was amazing and the coffee was even better. I got the vanilla lavender latte and it was the best latte I think I’ve ever had. Definitely would recommend for a comfy afternoon coffee or a work spot!

As a Washington transplant I am always looking for a great cup of coffee that has that Seattle vibe. Try this place- you won’t be disappointed. The atmosphere is inviting and comfortable for a work visit or catching up with friends. The coffee was the best I have had in quite a while. As a bonus- everyone who was working was friendly, asked questions to make sure we were getting just the right mix and we can’t wait to go back.

This was my first time visiting. Everybody was super friendly and easy to talk to.

There was plenty of comfy seating available while I enjoyed my yummy Maple Sunrise Latte.

I LOVE that they use real ceramic coffee mugs when you dine in.  Definitely a special touch that a lot of coffee shops have lost using all paper products.

I'll definitely be back!
Amazing coffee and lovely staff
Good coffee, neat place just, a little too big and loud for me.

In town visiting fam and stopped in for a quick coffee. Love the space and the employees are great.

The coffee wasn't my favorite.  Definitely on the more expensive end.

I usually take light cream in my coffee but don't recommend doing that here. The Americano was so hot that it did something funky with the cream and didn't taste great. I went back in, and they happily made me a new drink and didn't add cream.
Atmosphere was so warm and relaxing. Beautiful inside. Coffee was great and the staff was wonderful. This will be our new local coffee shop we go to.

One of the nicest coffee shops I've ever been to as far as the interior and atmosphere are concerned. The coffee was on par with any good local coffee shop I've been to.

The coffee is good, and the service and location are great.
The best coffee in the greater Charlotte area, hands down.
One of the best lattes I’ve ever had in the US. Definitely a must. Their Mountaineer is delicious.

Perfect Coffee and Perfect Venue. Coffee doesnt come any better than this. The shop has every attention to detail including the super comfy chairs at the window. Its a destination that suits those that work in coffee shops instead of at home as well as a casual meeting place for friends and co workers. Did I mention the coffee is to die for.

What a cute place. The space is open and relaxing with still plenty of places to sit and have  some privacy. Coffee was phenomenal. I got an almond milk cappuccino and it was sooo good. Stop by if you can!
I had coffee with a friend. My first time at Defined Coffee. Delicious products and quaint atmosphere. I'll be back soon.

Love this place and their love of coffee shines! Beautifully decorated, family friendly and willing to help someone with decidaphobia pick from their seasonal coffees…and I’ve love every one. Their pumpkin flavor is my favorite right now.

Very friendly service, great open space.  Lots of places to work on an electronic device and plugs close by the seating.  Chill vibe with open windows for natural lighting.  Tried a lovely hot tea while there.
Love this place! It’s beautiful, relaxing and welcoming! The drinks are delicious as well!

Defined coffee’s 3rd location is an outstanding one! They have started to roast their beans! The coffee is perfection. The atmosphere is ideal for a quick stop or a work from coffee-shop experience. The baristas are awesome, dedicated employees that are loyal to the brand and company. I can’t wait to bring people in here. Such a great job everyone!
Best coffee shop in Mooresville, hands down!!

Best cup of coffee I've had since moving to the Charlotte area. Kindest, most knowledgeable, and accommodating staff I've encountered at any establishment in the area.  And top notch design & aesthetic!
The best coffee in the Lake Norman area. Seeing the roaster inside the shop is also really cool! You get to see how the whole process happens
Great coffee and atmosphere! The staff was very welcoming. Great spot to get some work done or just chill out!
The best coffee around! Lovely atmosphere! Great place for a playdate. They have a little kids section with books and puzzles and comfy bean bag seats!
